-- WellPoint boosts share buyback program by $5 bln
-- By Shailesh Kuber
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 05:47PM EDT
-- None



Oct 2 (Reuters) - U.S. health insurer WellPoint Inc <WLP.N> increased its share repurchase authorization by $5 billion, taking the total program to $6 billion, the company said in a regulatory filing.

WellPoint's shares were up 1 percent after closing at $118.45 on the New York Stock Exchange on Thursday. WellPoint, which runs Anthem and Empire Blue Cross Blue Shield Plans, said the authorization is for a multi-year period. (http://1.usa.gov/1oFGu5U)